('DOC-030', 'QBR Call Summary', 'Q2 QBR: Acme Financial Services - Renewal Risk Discussion', 'West', 'Enterprise', 'Acme Financial Services',
 '2026-06-15',
 'Q2 2026 QBR with Acme Financial Services. Attendees: Customer - CFO, VP Data Engineering, Head of Procurement; Internal - Account Executive, Customer Success Manager, VP Engineering. Key discussion points: (1) INC-0001 impact review: Customer reiterated that the 6h47m outage caused material business disruption to regulatory reporting. CFO stated: "Our board has asked me to present cloud vendor risk assessment at the July meeting. I need ammunition to justify continued investment." (2) SLA credit: $520K credit approved and applied. (3) Renewal discussion: Current contract expires 2026-08-15 at $4.2M ARR. Customer indicated they will not sign a 3-year term without: (a) enhanced SLA of 99.99% with meaningful penalties, (b) dedicated infrastructure option, (c) executive-level reliability review quarterly. (4) Competitive pressure: Customer confirmed receiving proposals from two competitors. VP Engineering presented reliability roadmap including rack diversity, enhanced monitoring, and sub-5-minute failover target. Customer response: "Directionally positive but we need to see execution, not just plans." Renewal probability assessed at 55% for 3-year, 75% for 1-year at current terms. Revenue at risk: $4.2M.'),

('DOC-031', 'QBR Call Summary', 'Q2 QBR: TechNova Solutions - Churn Prevention Escalation', 'West', 'Enterprise', 'TechNova Solutions',
 '2026-06-14',
 'Q2 2026 QBR with TechNova Solutions. Attendees: Customer - CTO, VP Platform Engineering, Procurement Lead; Internal - Account Executive, Customer Success Director, Sr. Solutions Architect. Critical account status: HIGH CHURN RISK. Key points: (1) CTO opened by stating: "I have two signed proposals on my desk from competitors. The only reason I am in this meeting is the switching cost. Give me a reason to stay." (2) INC-0001 impact: 3 hours of complete unavailability for fraud detection pipeline, $890K unprocessed transactions. Customer states this is unacceptable for their use case. (3) Demands for renewal: 99.99% SLA, dedicated compute isolation, 24/7 premium support with 5-minute response time, and 25% price reduction to offset "risk premium." (4) Competitive landscape: Customer showed live demo of competitor environment they have been testing for 6 weeks. (5) Action items: Executive escalation to our CRO, custom reliability proposal within 5 business days, dedicated SE assigned full-time for 90 days. Renewal probability: 35%. Revenue at risk: $2.8M ARR. Renewal date: 2026-07-31 (IMMINENT).'),

('DOC-032', 'QBR Call Summary', 'Q2 QBR: Pacific Mutual Insurance - Confidence Rebuilding', 'West', 'Enterprise', 'Pacific Mutual Insurance',
 '2026-06-16',
 'Q2 2026 QBR with Pacific Mutual Insurance. Attendees: Customer - CIO, SVP Claims Technology, Vendor Management Director; Internal - Account Executive, Customer Success Manager, Engineering Director. Tone: concerned but constructive. Key discussion: (1) INC-0001 impact: 14,000 claims processing backlog, full recovery took 36 hours including data reconciliation. CIO stated: "We have invested heavily in this platform. We want to stay but our board is asking hard questions about single-vendor risk." (2) SLA credit: $340K credit request approved. (3) Positive signals: Customer acknowledged our transparent communication during incident and rapid post-incident follow-up. CIO: "Your response after the fact has been excellent. The question is prevention, not response." (4) Renewal positioning: Customer open to renewal if we deliver: enhanced monitoring dashboard with real-time SLA tracking, quarterly executive reliability reviews, and priority placement on new infrastructure when available. (5) Next steps: Technical deep-dive on new rack diversity architecture scheduled for 2026-06-25. Renewal probability: 70%. Contract: $3.1M ARR, renewal 2026-09-30.'),

('DOC-033', 'QBR Call Summary', 'Q2 QBR: Western Digital Analytics - Reliability Roadmap Review', 'West', 'Enterprise', 'Western Digital Analytics',
 '2026-06-18',
 'Q2 2026 QBR with Western Digital Analytics. Attendees: Customer - CTO, Director of Data Platform, Sr. Data Engineer; Internal - Account Executive, Solutions Architect, Sr. SRE. Meeting focus: Technical deep-dive on reliability improvements post INC-0001. Key outcomes: (1) Presented new architecture: multi-AZ storage with synchronous replication, automated failover <2 minutes, rack diversity for accounts >$1M ARR. Customer CTO reaction: "This is what we expected from day one. Why did it take an outage to get here?" (2) Customer requested timeline commitments: multi-AZ by end of Q3, automated failover by end of Q4. We committed to Q3 for multi-AZ, Q4 target for failover. (3) Renewal discussion: Customer stated they will renew if (a) multi-AZ is delivered before their Aug 31 renewal date and their workloads are migrated, (b) SLA credits for INC-0001 ($180K) are applied immediately. (4) Expansion opportunity: if reliability is proven, customer has $800K expansion pipeline for new ML workloads. Renewal probability: 65%. Contract: $2.4M ARR.'),

('DOC-034', 'QBR Call Summary', 'Q2 QBR: Cascade Health Systems - Regulatory Compliance Focus', 'West', 'Enterprise', 'Cascade Health Systems',
 '2026-06-17',
 'Q2 2026 QBR with Cascade Health Systems. Attendees: Customer - CISO, Director of Analytics, Compliance Manager; Internal - Account Executive, Customer Success Manager, Security Architect. Key themes: (1) INC-0001 impact on compliance posture: Customer has upcoming HIPAA audit in August. They need documentation proving data integrity was maintained during the incident. Our engineering team provided formal attestation that no data corruption occurred. (2) Snowpipe recovery issue (CASE-88834): Customer satisfied with root cause explanation but requesting automated alerting when streams fail to resume. Feature request logged. (3) Renewal sentiment: Customer is pragmatic - switching costs in healthcare are extremely high. They will renew but are requesting enhanced compliance-specific SLA addendum. (4) Renewal risk driven primarily by procurement seeking 10% discount citing INC-0001 as leverage. Renewal probability: 85%. Revenue at risk: $1.9M ARR (potential 10% discount = $190K reduction).'),

('DOC-035', 'QBR Call Summary', 'Q2 QBR: Atlantic Commerce Group - Growth Discussion', 'East', 'Enterprise', 'Atlantic Commerce Group',
 '2026-06-20',
 'Q2 2026 QBR with Atlantic Commerce Group. Attendees: Customer - VP Data, Platform Architect; Internal - Account Executive, Solutions Architect. Extremely positive meeting. Customer praised platform stability (unaffected by INC-0001 as they are in East region). Key topics: (1) 45% YoY data growth, planning to expand from 2 to 5 warehouses. (2) Interested in new ML features for demand forecasting. (3) Renewal: early renewal discussion for December - customer interested in 3-year commit for volume pricing. No churn risk. Expansion pipeline: $600K. Account health: GREEN.'),

('DOC-036', 'QBR Call Summary', 'Q2 QBR: NovaPay Financial - Transaction SLA Remediation', 'West', 'Enterprise', 'NovaPay Financial',
 '2026-06-19',
 'Q2 2026 QBR with NovaPay Financial. Attendees: Customer - COO, VP Engineering, Legal Counsel; Internal - Account Executive, VP Customer Success, Engineering Director. Focus: remediation plan for transaction processing SLA breach during INC-0001. Key outcomes: (1) $215K SLA credit approved per contract terms. (2) Customer COO stated: "We have a strong 3-year partnership. One incident does not define a relationship, but the response to it does. Show us this cannot happen again." (3) Agreed deliverables: dedicated compute cluster for transaction workloads by July 1, real-time failover testing every 30 days with customer observation, enhanced monitoring with customer-visible dashboard. (4) Renewal: July 15 renewal date approaching. Customer will renew if dedicated compute is operational by then. Verbal commitment received. Renewal probability: 80%. Contract: $3.6M ARR.'),

('DOC-037', 'QBR Call Summary', 'Q2 QBR: Pinnacle Biotech - Audit Preparedness', 'West', 'Enterprise', 'Pinnacle Biotech',
 '2026-06-21',
 'Q2 2026 QBR with Pinnacle Biotech. Attendees: Customer - Chief Compliance Officer, Head of Data Science, Procurement; Internal - Account Executive, Customer Success Manager, Compliance Specialist. Key points: (1) INC-0001 FDA audit impact resolved - regulator accepted our formal incident documentation. Customer relieved but CCO stated: "We got lucky with the extension. If this happens during our November submission window, the consequences are severe." (2) Customer requesting: audit-window protection (guaranteed no maintenance during declared audit periods), enhanced SLA for compliance workloads, formal DR testing participation. (3) Renewal: September 15 date. Customer will renew but seeking enhanced compliance terms. Procurement using INC-0001 as negotiation leverage for 12% discount. Renewal probability: 78%. Revenue impact: potential $204K discount on $1.7M ARR.'),

