('DOC-050', 'Exec Escalation', 'ESCALATION: TechNova Solutions - CRO Direct Engagement Required', 'West', 'Enterprise', 'TechNova Solutions',
 '2026-06-15',
 'EXECUTIVE ESCALATION - URGENT. Account: TechNova Solutions. ARR: $2.8M. Renewal Date: 2026-07-31 (46 days). Escalation Reason: Account at imminent churn risk following INC-0001. CTO has competitive proposals and is actively testing alternative platform. Required Action: CRO direct engagement within 48 hours. Background: TechNova runs mission-critical fraud detection on our platform. INC-0001 caused 3 hours of unavailability, resulting in $890K of unprocessed transactions. CTO stated in QBR: "I have two signed proposals on my desk." Customer demands: 99.99% SLA, dedicated compute, 24/7 premium support, 25% price reduction. Recommended CRO approach: (1) Personal call acknowledging failure and committing to specific reliability guarantees. (2) Offer dedicated compute cluster at no additional cost for 12 months. (3) Enhanced SLA with meaningful penalties demonstrating skin in the game. (4) Dedicated SE for 90 days. (5) Innovation partnership: early access to new features. Do NOT offer price reduction as first lever - compete on value and commitment. Revenue at risk: $2.8M ARR. Probability of save with CRO engagement: 55%. Without: 20%.'),

('DOC-051', 'Exec Escalation', 'ESCALATION: Acme Financial Services - VP Sales West + VP Engineering Joint Response', 'West', 'Enterprise', 'Acme Financial Services',
 '2026-06-12',
 'EXECUTIVE ESCALATION. Account: Acme Financial Services. ARR: $4.2M (largest West Enterprise account). Renewal Date: 2026-08-15 (64 days). Escalation Reason: CFO explicitly stated renewal risk in QBR. Board-level cloud vendor review scheduled for July. Required Action: Joint response from VP Sales West and VP Engineering within 5 business days. Background: INC-0001 caused 6h47m of complete unavailability during month-end regulatory reporting. $520K SLA credit already applied. Customer requesting: enhanced SLA (99.99%), dedicated infrastructure, quarterly executive reliability reviews. CFO quote: "I need ammunition to justify continued investment at our board meeting." Recommended approach: (1) VP Engineering to present reliability roadmap in dedicated 90-minute session with customer technical team. (2) VP Sales to schedule dinner with CFO to discuss partnership vision and commercial framework. (3) Provide written executive commitment letter signed by our CEO addressing reliability investment. (4) Offer board-ready materials: reliability metrics, investment summary, roadmap timeline. (5) Propose Customer Advisory Board seat. Revenue at risk: $4.2M ARR. This is our highest-value account in West region. Probability of renewal with executive engagement: 70%. Current trajectory without intervention: 45%.'),

('DOC-052', 'Exec Escalation', 'ESCALATION: West Enterprise Portfolio Risk - CRO Strategic Review', 'West', 'Enterprise', 'ALL ACCOUNTS',
 '2026-06-14',
 'EXECUTIVE ESCALATION - PORTFOLIO LEVEL. To: CRO, CFO, VP Sales West, VP Customer Success. Subject: West Enterprise renewal portfolio at elevated risk following INC-0001. Summary: INC-0001 has created systemic renewal risk across the West Enterprise segment. Key metrics: Total West Enterprise ARR: $89.4M. Accounts with renewal risk >70: 241 accounts representing $52.3M ARR. Accounts with renewal in next 120 days and risk >75: 47 accounts representing $31.2M ARR. Estimated revenue at risk (probability-weighted): $14.8M. Immediate churn threats (renewal <60 days, risk >85): TechNova Solutions ($2.8M, Jul 31), NovaPay Financial ($3.6M, Jul 15), Acme Financial Services ($4.2M, Aug 15). Recommended strategic actions: (1) Declare "West Enterprise Save Sprint" - dedicate executive team capacity for 90 days. (2) Allocate $2.1M in SLA credits and commercial concessions budget. (3) Accelerate reliability roadmap deliverables for West region. (4) Assign named executive sponsor to every account >$2M with risk >80. (5) Weekly CRO review of save progress. (6) Authorize dedicated compute for top-10 accounts at risk. If executed immediately, projected save rate: 72% of at-risk ARR. Delay of 2+ weeks reduces projected save rate to 58%.'),

('DOC-053', 'Exec Escalation', 'ESCALATION: Redwood Capital Management - Legal Threat', 'West', 'Enterprise', 'Redwood Capital Management',
 '2026-06-16',
 'EXECUTIVE ESCALATION. Account: Redwood Capital Management. ARR: $2.9M. Renewal Date: 2026-09-01. Escalation Reason: Customer legal counsel has sent formal letter demanding: (1) Full forensic data integrity audit for all customer data during INC-0001 window, (2) Written guarantee that no data was corrupted, modified, or lost, (3) Independent third-party verification. Context: Customer initially found 47 NULL values in pricing table after INC-0001. Joint investigation confirmed NULLs pre-date incident (upstream data quality issue). Customer acknowledged this but legal team is using it as basis for broader data integrity demand. Risk: If not handled carefully, could escalate to formal legal claim or regulatory complaint. Recommended approach: (1) Our General Counsel to respond to customer legal team within 48 hours. (2) Offer independent third-party audit at our cost (estimated $150K). (3) Provide formal written data integrity attestation from VP Engineering. (4) Schedule executive call (our CLO + their GC) to de-escalate. (5) Separate legal track from renewal track - do not let legal team drive renewal discussion. Renewal risk: 74/100. Legal risk: MEDIUM-HIGH.'),

('DOC-054', 'Exec Escalation', 'ESCALATION: Summit Analytics Group - Competitive Win-Back Attempt', 'West', 'Enterprise', 'Summit Analytics Group',
