('DOC-063', 'QBR Call Summary', 'Q2 QBR: Velocity Logistics - Contract Penalty Resolution', 'West', 'Enterprise', 'Velocity Logistics',
 '2026-06-23',
 'Q2 2026 QBR with Velocity Logistics. Attendees: Customer - VP Technology, Legal Director, Procurement Manager; Internal - Account Executive, Deal Desk, Legal. Focus: Resolving contractual penalty clause triggered by INC-0001. Key discussion: (1) Customer contract has non-standard clause: <99.9% monthly uptime triggers automatic 15% discount on next renewal. May uptime: 99.87% per customer measurement. (2) Our legal team confirmed clause is valid and enforceable. (3) Negotiation: Offered alternative - instead of 15% discount ($375K/year reduction), proposed: $200K immediate credit + enhanced SLA + dedicated support for 12 months. Customer legal team to review. (4) Customer VP Technology stated: "The penalty clause exists for exactly this reason. We are not trying to extract value - we are trying to ensure you take our uptime seriously." (5) Positive note: Customer confirmed they plan to renew regardless of penalty resolution. Issue is commercial terms, not churn risk. Renewal probability: 90% (terms TBD). Contract: $2.5M ARR, renewal 2026-10-01.'),

