('DOC-080', 'Incident Postmortem', 'INC-0001 Lessons Learned: Platform Engineering Retrospective', 'West', 'Enterprise', 'ALL ACCOUNTS',
 '2026-06-30',
 'INC-0001 Platform Engineering Retrospective - Final. Key lessons: (1) Change freeze policies must exempt critical reliability patches. The firmware fix was available 2 weeks before the incident but deployment was blocked by month-end change freeze. New policy: reliability and security patches are exempt from change freezes with VP Engineering approval. (2) Blast radius management: Rack affinity rules allowed multiple high-value tenants to co-locate on adjacent racks. New requirement: accounts >$1M ARR must be distributed across minimum 3 rack groups. (3) Thermal monitoring gaps: Existing alerts triggered at 75C (too late). New threshold: automated workload migration at 68C, alert at 65C. (4) Failover speed: Current failover to secondary storage took 2+ hours. Investment approved for synchronous replication enabling <2 minute failover (target: Q4 delivery). (5) Customer communication: First customer notification was 43 minutes after incident declaration. New target: <15 minutes. Automated status page update pipeline deployed. (6) Recovery validation: Snowpipe streams did not auto-resume for some customers. Fix deployed: automated stream health check and restart 5 minutes after service restoration confirmed. Total engineering investment in reliability improvements: $12M allocated for FY2027.');
